Around 30% of adults with ADHD also experiencing depression. ð§  

Living with both can feel like a constant push and pullâwhile ADHD brings bursts of energy and impulsivity, depression can make it hard to feel motivated or engaged. 

This combination creates unique challenges, impacting focus, self-esteem, and daily functioning.

Why do ADHD and depression so often occur together? 

For many, the struggles of managing ADHD symptoms can lead to feelings of frustration, isolation, and low self-worth, especially when they feel misunderstood or judged by others. 

ADHD brains also have differences in dopamine regulation, affecting both mood and motivation, which can increase the risk of developing depression. 

Recognizing this overlap is crucial for finding the right support and treatments, and for addressing both conditions holistically. 

Remember, youâre not alone, and help is available. ð

ð This is the secret to marinating tofu like a pro!

Marinating tofu straight from the fridge might make the outside taste good, but sorry to say it, it leaves the middle kind of bland ð¤·ââï¸

If you want your marinade to really add flavour - and give your tofu a meatier texture - the trick is to freeze it first. Fully freeze it, fully thaw it, drain the excess water and then gently hand press out a little more of the water.

After that, throw it in your marinade. Slices, cubes or chunks of tofu - this method will improve them all. Then just cook it with whatever you prefer (lots of inspo on our grid!)
